+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013ZGPeCdkBF9GUX67j4LFQ2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n     2→\n     3→Add the ability to defer tasks so they only become available for processing after a specified time.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- A task can be given a delay (in milliseconds) or a specific future time at which it becomes available.\n     8→- Delayed tasks are added to the queue immediately but are not returned when retrieving until their availability time has passed.\n     9→- Non-delayed tasks are always preferred over delayed tasks that are not yet available.\n    10→- When multiple delayed tasks become available simultaneously, they should be ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO.\n    11→- The task object should indicate when it becomes available.\n    12→- Delays work correctly with named queues.\n    13→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PCETeDdzoFcSGHJpsaPbiM","session_id":"b7255fb0-57ab-4a91-9486-5bfa4e4e7cc3","uuid":"c24c910b-be5d-45a2-ad35-fd305140e3de"}
