asks with millisecond delays or specific availability times\n- Delayed tasks added but not returned until available\n- Availability time ordering, then priority, then FIFO\n- Task object shows availability time\n\n**Phase 5: Retry with Backoff**\n- Mark tasks as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks auto-re-added with exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt-1)`\n- Configurable max retries (default: 3) and base delay (default: 1000ms)\n- Track attempt count\n- Exhausted retries leave task in failed state\n\n**Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue (DLQ)**\n- Failed tasks move to DLQ after exhausting retries\n- View dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Move DLQ tasks back for fresh retries\n- Clear DLQ\n- Per-queue independent DLQ\n\n**Phase 7: Task Dependencies**\n- Tasks can depend on other task IDs\n- Blocked tasks not returned until dependencies complete\n- Detect and reject circular dependencies at creation time\n- Failed dependencies keep dependents blocked\n- Inspect dependency status\n\n**Phase 8: Concurrency Control**\n- Per-queue max concurrency limits\n- Retrieving task returns null if concurrency limit reached\n- Completing/failing tasks frees slots\n- Default: unlimited concurrency\n- Query concurrency limit and active count\n- Respects priority ordering\n\n**Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation**\n- Processing tasks report progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates\n- Cancellable subscriptions\n- Cancel pending or processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n**Phase 10: Recurring Tasks**\n- Cron-like schedules with simple expressions:\n  - `*/N * * * *` - every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` - every hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` - every day at midnight\n- Create, remove, list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism to check and enqueue due tasks\n- Recurring tasks become regular tasks after enqueuing\n\n**Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline**\n- Register middleware per queue\n- Tasks pass through middleware in order before handler\n- Middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Middleware can modify/transform tasks\n- Middleware errors mark task as failed\n- Per-queue handler after middleware\n- Independent middleware stack per queue\n\n**Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown**\n- Stop accepting new tasks on shutdown\n- Wait for processing tasks (configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancel tasks exceeding timeout\n- Register shutdown callbacks\n- Return summary (completed, cancelled, duration)\n- Multiple shutdown calls safe\n- Immediate completion if no tasks processing\n\n## Development Guidelines\n\n**Scripts available:**\n```bash\nnpm run build   # TypeScript compilation to /dist\nnpm run lint    # ESLint check on /src\nnpm run test    # Vitest runner\n```\n\n**Export from:** `/workspace/src/index.ts`\n\n**Design considerations noted in TASK.md:**\n- Design with extensibility in mind - later phases force rethinking early decisions\n- Tasks need unique identifiers and lifecycle status tracking\n- Consider how priorities, delays, and dependencies interact"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0dc4a7 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 17976\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 23153</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7255fb0-57ab-4a91-9486-5bfa4e4e7cc3","uuid":"bac3d51e-71a3-43bd-8d71-bded02c7d879","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the full project structure. I need to understand:\n1. What files exist in the project root and their contents\n2. What's in the phases/ directory (all .md files)\n3. What's in the src/ directory\n4. The package.json, tsconfig.json, and any other config files\n5. The TASK.md file\n\nRead ALL phase files (phases/01.md through phases/12.md) completely. Read package.json, tsconfig.json, and any eslint config. Read TASK.md. List all files in src/.","agentId":"a0dc4a7","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've completed the full exploration of your 